Title: Let your soul shine through your Words
DateModified: '2019-02-28'
DatePublished: '2019-02-28'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/let-your-soul-shine-through-your-words
SetInCountry: India
Category: Making a local connection
AuthorName: Sandhya Dhavala
AuthorCountry: India
Text: "This story is about ama amazing place in south India called Coorg, known as\
  \ natures paradise. Think the name is justified because u enjoy nature in your each\
  \ and every move of the place. \nMe with a bunch of friends wanted to do something\
  \ unconventional for new years and decided to go and explore coorg.\nWe reached\
  \ coorg through public transportation and went got ourselves a hotel( which is cheap\
  \ and good), got freshedup and leaped into the town.\nAs we know India is also known\
  \ as the home of elephants we went to all elephant sanctuary and camps and played\
  \ with this big creatures, then relaxed at boat kayaking. Been to few other nature\
  \ views nearby and headed back at night.\n\nThe best part about this place is u\
  \ can do rowing, trekking and all the possible adventures you love.\nWe went to\
  \ local guy place near a mountain and started trekking for 14 kms.\nCame back and\
  \ we took some essentials and went up again for bonfire camping.\nImagine yourself\
  \ on top of world under zillions of stars on 31st December with campfire. Isn\u2019\
  t it gives you goosebumps \U0001F481\U0001F3FB\u200D\u2640\uFE0F.\nYes it does...\n\
  \nOn our 3rd and 4th day we went to different places like waterfalls, widelife sanctuary\
  \ made connections with the local people, understood their culture their habits\
  \ and how they treat their mother nature...\n\n\nThis is my first travel story and\
  \ which is very close to me.\nAfter this i had many travels in northern part of\
  \ Australia and many little adventures here."
